      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CROYDON REIGN (8) is generally an honest type in the frame at one of 12 starts but missed the placings last time when fifth (23.07) over 395m at Murray Bridge. Has never been out of the money in five starts this distance. Drawn wide but with a clean break will be tough to beat again. NATIONAL GRID (1) was midfield throughout and finished there last time when 5th (17.58) at this track. Has a strong record out of this box with four wins and four minor placings from 10 starts. Can do much better this time. STORM SISTER (4) was below best at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth at this track, but was among the placings at this track three back. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. SEBON DISCO (2) deserves plenty of thought over this trip.",
